  "text": "This gives the estimate of overfitting in the neural network (R train > R test ), i.e, higher the generalisation error more the overfitting. This estimate of fault tolerance is used for evaluation of different Neural Networks throughout the paper. Fault Model. In this work, the fault occurring in the hardware is simulated in the form of stuck at \"0\" errors in the Neural network computation. Further, multiple faults can occur simultaneously for which the goal is measure the performance of the model using test accuracy. The faults are simulated in two major ways: firstly, these faults can manifest in the form of random node crashes in the Neural Network due to which the output of the neurone is always put to zero. Secondly, the parameters of the Neural Networks can be stuck at \"0\" which includes both the weights in case of Multi Layer Perceptron and the filter and kernel values in case of convolutional neural networks. This is a common fault model frequently used in evaluating the reliability of systems [CITATION_1] .",
